880
01:12:05,276 --> 01:12:06,612
No shit?

881
01:12:38,279 --> 01:12:39,788
Mimi Lurie...

882
01:12:43,584 --> 01:12:46,563
and Henry Osborne.

883
01:12:54,969 --> 01:12:56,676
It doesn't make sense.

884
01:13:13,478 --> 01:13:15,790
Where are you going?

885
01:13:26,587 --> 01:13:28,535
Let's go. You can
walk me to class.

886
01:13:28,727 --> 01:13:29,976
Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

887
01:13:31,575 --> 01:13:34,132
So, tell me about yourself.
- Peace Corp for a bit,

888
01:13:35,979 --> 01:13:37,703
thought I was gonna change the world,

889
01:13:38,280 --> 01:13:41,116
decided it was actually people
who needed changing,

890
01:13:41,884 --> 01:13:46,121
went back to school to study psychology,
turns out psychology has nothing to do with that,

891
01:13:47,668 --> 01:13:49,920
ended up in New York, for a bit...

892
01:13:50,981 --> 01:13:52,915
I guess I thought I was gonna change myself,

893
01:13:53,685 --> 01:13:55,704
turns out I'm too stubborn.

894
01:13:55,897 --> 01:13:57,532
You must be older than I thought.

895
01:14:00,179 --> 01:14:02,914
So, what happens now?
If in doubt, you go back to law school?

896
01:14:03,990 --> 01:14:07,609
I'm not in doubt.
It's my mom, she's a judge.

897
01:14:08,186 --> 01:14:13,208
Really? So was mine!
Just not professionally.

898
01:14:18,896 --> 01:14:20,311
You like Michigan?

899
01:14:21,491 --> 01:14:22,903
I love it.

900
01:14:24,191 --> 01:14:25,691
Okay, you...

901
01:14:25,884 --> 01:14:29,194
I read one of your articles online last night.
I read a couple of them, actually.

902
01:14:29,291 --> 01:14:31,636
You're kidding me? Really?
And what'd you think?

903
01:14:33,384 --> 01:14:35,721
I think you broke a big story.
- I did!

904
01:14:36,882 --> 01:14:40,060
I think you're clinging to it like a life-raft.
- Oh, ho, ho.... wow.

905
01:14:40,061 --> 01:14:41,703
and now it defines you.
- Wow!

906
01:14:41,801 --> 01:14:44,625
Yeah, I do.
- Maybe psych's not a bad fit after all.

907
01:14:46,389 --> 01:14:48,506
I kinda call 'em like I see 'em.

908
01:14:48,793 --> 01:14:51,321
Fair enough, call this one.
Your father's ignoring me, why?

909
01:14:52,583 --> 01:14:54,930
I'm guessing because... he doesn't want to talk to you?

910
01:14:56,563 --> 01:14:59,610
Hmm...
- He's retired.

911
01:15:00,986 --> 01:15:06,507
I mean, and this was decades ago.
He wants to fish, and watch boats on the water...

912
01:15:07,595 --> 01:15:11,103
He's also not one for reminiscing.

913
01:15:12,396 --> 01:15:14,617
You know he was close to the Lurie family?

914
01:15:15,788 --> 01:15:21,984
Yeah. Her dad and my granddad
were fishing buddies, I think.

915
01:15:23,092 --> 01:15:27,384
Yeah, so I heard.
- Yeah, they used to go up to the Linder Woods in the U.P.

916
01:15:27,481 --> 01:15:30,400
It's absolutely gorgeous
up there, you would hate it.

917
01:15:30,497 --> 01:15:33,106
The "U.P."?
- The upper peninsula.

918
01:15:34,398 --> 01:15:36,150
He told me he never met her.

919
01:15:38,450 --> 01:15:39,696
Huh!

920
01:15:42,098 --> 01:15:45,889
Had to be hard, live with the Lurie name
after everything went down.

921
01:15:45,890 --> 01:15:48,394
Yeah. I'm sure it was.

922
01:15:49,194 --> 01:15:50,935
You ever talk about her
when you were younger?

923
01:15:51,995 --> 01:15:54,119
This was all way before my time.

924
01:16:01,499 --> 01:16:02,920
What are you thinking?

925
01:16:06,404 --> 01:16:09,212
Can I speak honestly with you for a second?
- Yeah.

926
01:16:10,792 --> 01:16:12,228
People lie for two reasons.

927
01:16:12,612 --> 01:16:16,212
They speak unknowingly, a simple mistake, y' know.
Or they do it intentionally,

928
01:16:16,404 --> 01:16:19,324
and having met a known fugitive who's also
a family friend isn't something you would forget.

929
01:16:19,420 --> 01:16:21,021
Mm... what are you getting at?

930
01:16:21,405 --> 01:16:24,237
In my business, when someone lies
intentionally, that's significant.

931
01:16:25,397 --> 01:16:28,421
It seems your father lied to me,
I'm guessing it's some way to cover himself.

932
01:16:28,901 --> 01:16:33,717
Look, Ben, I get that you're good
at your job, but so is my dad,

933
01:16:33,813 --> 01:16:37,506
and I would put the quality of his character
up against anyone in the world.

934
01:16:37,602 --> 01:16:41,282
So, if you're insinuating that he was
or is somehow involved in something

935
01:16:41,283 --> 01:16:45,818
that ends up in your paper? I would be damn sure
you know what you're talking about.

936
01:16:46,396 --> 01:16:48,618
I may be a student of the law, but that's libel,

937
01:16:48,715 --> 01:16:51,139
and in my business, that's significant.

938
01:16:55,795 --> 01:16:57,180
I'd like to see you again!

939
01:17:03,038 --> 01:17:04,324
Bye.

940
01:17:17,097 --> 01:17:19,314
Every sixth and seventh number.

941
01:17:20,198 --> 01:17:22,634
How do I know who I'm calling?
- You don't.

942
01:17:24,455 --> 01:17:26,346
Okay.
- Good luck.

943
01:17:48,604 --> 01:17:52,333
Hi, this is, uh, John Smith,
I'm looking for a plumber.

944
01:17:54,004 --> 01:17:56,697
Are you now?
- Yes, I am.

945
01:17:58,004 --> 01:18:02,604
Wow, been a long time since I've heard that.
- Is this line clean?

946
01:18:02,702 --> 01:18:05,938
Babe, they didn't listen to me back then,
and they sure ain't listenin' to me now.

947
01:18:06,710 --> 01:18:09,014
Who's calling?
- Nick Sloan.

948
01:18:10,397 --> 01:18:16,842
Nick Sloan? God, I just saw you on TV.
- Unless you wanna see yourself there too, we'd better hurry.

949
01:18:17,803 --> 01:18:19,927
I need to get to Mimi Lurie.

950
01:18:21,408 --> 01:18:26,616
Where are you?
- 845-555-8249.

951
01:18:28,411 --> 01:18:31,516
Okay, I'll see if we still got the juice.

952
01:18:32,097 --> 01:18:33,531
Hang tight, brother.

953
01:18:45,597 --> 01:18:50,121
You wanna hear somethin' funny?
I've been Jim Grant longer than I've been me.

954
01:18:50,312 --> 01:18:51,628
That's nice.

955
01:18:54,010 --> 01:18:55,937
Come on, Jed, we're just talking here.

956
01:18:56,610 --> 01:18:57,742
We don't need to talk.

957
01:18:59,101 --> 01:19:02,934
I think we do, you're angry.
- You're damn right I am.

958
01:19:04,006 --> 01:19:07,626
Jesus. Thirty years on, still holding a grudge, huh?

959
01:19:07,819 --> 01:19:09,243
No...

960
01:19:10,615 --> 01:19:12,826
it was the lack of respect.

961
01:19:13,119 --> 01:19:16,627
You guys put everybody in danger.
We didn't kill anybody, we didn't hurt anyone.

962
01:19:16,914 --> 01:19:18,667
We were a peace movement,
for christ's sake!

963
01:19:20,916 --> 01:19:22,739
People make mistakes, Jed.

964
01:19:24,936 --> 01:19:27,829
Then you turn yourself in and
atone for what you've done,

965
01:19:27,925 --> 01:19:30,552
and then you keep up the struggle
in any small way you can.

966
01:19:31,712 --> 01:19:33,237
You like what you're doing now?

967
01:19:34,209 --> 01:19:35,634
Yeah.

968
01:19:36,307 --> 01:19:39,844
Yeah! I like what I try to do...
I like my students.

969
01:19:40,517 --> 01:19:42,118
Seems like it's mutual.

970
01:19:42,694 --> 01:19:46,254
Yeah... I can still pack the hall when I...

971
01:19:48,005 --> 01:19:49,630
..talk about SDS.

972
01:19:51,306 --> 01:19:53,634
March on Washington,
trying to change the world,

973
01:19:53,730 --> 01:19:55,635
they're drawn to it, I can tell.

974
01:19:56,611 --> 01:19:58,143
They just don't know
what to do with it.

975
01:19:58,719 --> 01:20:01,155
I don't know why they would,
it's ancient history to them.

976
01:20:02,503 --> 01:20:03,635
So they listen and clap,

977
01:20:03,731 --> 01:20:07,314
and then they update their Facebook
statuses and they forget all about it.

978
01:20:07,411 --> 01:20:09,452
We've turned into our parents, Jed.
- Yeah,

979
01:20:10,711 --> 01:20:12,868
now we're just a story told to children.

980
01:20:14,879 --> 01:20:18,368
Well, I'm glad someone's still telling it.

981
01:20:24,008 --> 01:20:26,639
- Yeah.
- You the guy that needs a plumber?

982
01:20:27,121 --> 01:20:31,717
I am. Line clean?
- Thirty seconds to be safe.

983
01:20:31,814 --> 01:20:33,522
Mimi?
- Was here, yeah.

984
01:20:33,618 --> 01:20:35,242
Here?
- Big Sur.

985
01:20:36,011 --> 01:20:38,125
Was?
- Left yesterday.

986
01:20:38,805 --> 01:20:40,735
Say where going?
- North.

987
01:20:41,221 --> 01:20:45,039
By boat?
- Woulda' made more sense, but she was headin' inland.

988
01:20:45,423 --> 01:20:47,627
Got it.
- Good luck!

989
01:20:49,031 --> 01:20:50,595
She gone?

990
01:20:50,999 --> 01:20:54,438
Yeah...
but I know where she's headed.

991
01:20:55,923 --> 01:20:58,748
Hey? Thanks for everything.

992
01:20:59,520 --> 01:21:02,755
You really want to thank me, Nick,
you'll never contact me again.

993
01:21:37,719 --> 01:21:40,429
Everything we have on the reporter,
he's been in Michigan for two days.

994
01:21:40,623 --> 01:21:43,231
Background on people he's contacted
and places he's visited.

995
01:21:43,326 --> 01:21:45,468
Stay on him.
- Of course, sir. Travel safe.

996
01:22:02,025 --> 01:22:03,458
Can I see some ID, please?

997
01:22:05,028 --> 01:22:08,240
Alright, thank you Mr. Haywood.
Have a good day.

998
01:22:17,731 --> 01:22:20,246
I'm looking for real estate records and plat maps?

999
01:22:20,727 --> 01:22:25,555
Lurie family, Linder-Lurie Lumber,
and Linder Holdings... going back 50 years.

1000
01:22:28,031 --> 01:22:29,247
Those three.

1001
01:22:32,826 --> 01:22:34,367
Agent Cornelius, welcome back...

1002
01:22:36,731 --> 01:22:38,147
Right this way.

1003
01:22:49,129 --> 01:22:52,352
So, where are the Linder Woods?
- I have no idea.

1004
01:22:53,629 --> 01:22:59,241
What about Drummond Island?
- It's up here, right across the water from Canada.

1005
01:22:59,533 --> 01:23:02,838
And this white part, this is private property, right?
- Beats me.

1006
01:23:02,934 --> 01:23:07,242
I mean, it's not part of that... that conservancy,
or that preserve, or whatever that is?

1007
01:23:07,653 --> 01:23:13,850
No... it doesn't look like it.
I don't see any sales, or state seizure reports.

1008
01:23:14,735 --> 01:23:17,569
But if this is privatly owned, somebody's
still paying taxes on this, right?

1009
01:23:18,339 --> 01:23:19,755
I don't know.

1010
01:23:20,636 --> 01:23:22,455
Can I have copies of all this?
- Sure.

1011
01:23:54,605 --> 01:23:59,474
I'm standing outside the Ann Arbor courthouse
where Sharon Solarz entered a plea of "not guilty."

1012
01:23:59,956 --> 01:24:01,587
Judge Panomino remanded her without bail...

1013
01:24:01,810 --> 01:24:03,653
Mr. Osbourne, can I speak to you?
- Not now.

1014
01:24:03,750 --> 01:24:05,878
Not talking to me is a very
dangerous decision for you right now.

1015
01:24:10,827 --> 01:24:13,531
Not here, I'll call you.
- Look, if I don't hear from you soon, this is...

1016
01:24:13,532 --> 01:24:14,863
You will.

1017
01:26:16,533 --> 01:26:19,357
Don't bother cleaning up,
we won't be here that long.

1018
01:26:27,454 --> 01:26:28,874
You came.

1019
01:26:38,334 --> 01:26:39,680
You look older.

1020
01:26:42,848 --> 01:26:45,376
You look the same.
- Yeah, right.

1021
01:26:51,748 --> 01:26:54,752
Mi, we gotta talk.
- So, talk.

1022
01:26:56,041 --> 01:26:57,768
Come on, Mimi, is this the way
you're gonna play it?

1023
01:26:57,961 --> 01:27:00,456
Like we don't know each other?
Like I'm just some adversary?

1024
01:27:00,552 --> 01:27:02,558
Aren't you?
- Don't...

1025
01:27:02,606 --> 01:27:05,861
Okay, so why am I here?
Why did you smoke me out?

1026
01:27:05,862 --> 01:27:08,274
"Smoke you out"?
- You went to Donal.

1027
01:27:08,849 --> 01:27:10,998
I had to.
- Well, I got the message, I'm here.

1028
01:27:14,346 --> 01:27:16,573
Nick, I can't help you,
that's why I'm here.

1029
01:27:16,670 --> 01:27:19,582
I came to tell you.
I figured I owed you that.

1030
01:27:25,113 --> 01:27:26,362
Hmm.

1031
01:27:28,956 --> 01:27:31,862
I have a daughter.
- I know.

1032
01:27:33,052 --> 01:27:34,679
She's almost twelve.

1033
01:27:40,163 --> 01:27:41,480
That's her.

1034
01:27:46,640 --> 01:27:50,293
What's her name?
- Isabel.

1035
01:27:51,353 --> 01:27:52,888
Your middle name, yeah.

1036
01:27:54,861 --> 01:27:56,496
Didn't you love your wife?

1037
01:27:59,350 --> 01:28:02,962
More than you can imagine.
- Oh, I can imagine...

1038
01:28:03,154 --> 01:28:07,077
Look, I know this child. She's probably never gonna
get over what's happened to her already,

1039
01:28:07,271 --> 01:28:09,086
and she's got a whole life ahead of her.

1040
01:28:10,046 --> 01:28:12,591
So, I'm asking you just to...
- You're asking me

1041
01:28:13,363 --> 01:28:18,682
to give myself up, so I can
clear you, for the sake of the child.

1042
01:28:20,551 --> 01:28:24,567
I see... everything to protect
the new little family.

1043
01:28:25,047 --> 01:28:28,612
Fuck your principles, fuck anything
else you used to stand for?

1044
01:28:30,444 --> 01:28:33,671
Well, the struggle doesn't end
just because you got tired of it.

1045
01:28:33,768 --> 01:28:36,584
I didn't get tired of it,
I grew up.

1046
01:28:37,356 --> 01:28:40,712
We promised each other we weren't going to do that.
- Yeah, but it happened.

1047
01:28:45,561 --> 01:28:47,336
I left the movement for the same
reason I joined it

1048
01:28:47,434 --> 01:28:50,241
because I didn't want to see good people's
lives thrown away for nothing.

1049
01:28:52,478 --> 01:28:56,090
You've waited a long time
to tell me that, haven't you?

1050
01:28:57,762 --> 01:29:00,302
And you've been a long time
coming home from the bank.

1051
01:29:05,270 --> 01:29:06,808
You were close to Mimi Lurie's family.

1052
01:29:08,847 --> 01:29:11,087
I wouldn't say close,
my dad knew her dad.

1053
01:29:13,263 --> 01:29:17,471
You went to the same school, same church,
you went on fishing trips together.

1054
01:29:19,159 --> 01:29:20,594
There's something you're not telling me.

1055
01:29:22,228 --> 01:29:23,472
What are you driving at, Shepard?

1056
01:29:23,472 --> 01:29:26,964
We know that Nick Sloan is looking
for something or someone to clear him.

1057
01:29:27,060 --> 01:29:29,210
I know that's your assumption.
- Could that be Mimi Lurie?

1058
01:29:32,654 --> 01:29:33,969
I'm off the record.

1059
01:29:37,149 --> 01:29:40,869
Think it out. First he'd have to find
her, and convince her to testify.

1060
01:29:40,966 --> 01:29:42,585
Second, she'd have to surrender.

1061
01:29:43,065 --> 01:29:45,504
But it's a participants testimony.
- That's the point.

1062
01:29:46,754 --> 01:29:51,570
If Mimi comes out of hiding, and surrenders herself
to testify that Nick Sloan wasn't at the bank,

1063
01:29:51,666 --> 01:29:53,799
it's what lawyers call a declaration against interest.

1064
01:29:54,279 --> 01:29:57,974
Destroys her own possibility of a defense.
It would clear him.

1065
01:29:58,071 --> 01:30:01,587
Why? Why would she do that? Why would she
give herself up to a jail sentence to save him?

1066
01:30:01,972 --> 01:30:04,571
I mean, what is her motivation?
You really she's gonna do that?

1067
01:30:04,572 --> 01:30:06,007
Don't matter what we think.

1068
01:30:07,159 --> 01:30:09,428
He obviously believes he can convince her.
- Why now?

1069
01:30:11,360 --> 01:30:13,077
Why not do this back then?

1070
01:30:16,461 --> 01:30:18,093
How long have you known about this?

1071
01:30:20,169 --> 01:30:22,586
I'm obviously not the only person in this conversation

1072
01:30:22,681 --> 01:30:26,022
who knows about her ties to a piece of
property just on the other side of Canada.

1073
01:30:28,429 --> 01:30:31,348
Mr. Osborne, what's the actual charge
against a law enforcement officer who

1074
01:30:31,349 --> 01:30:34,274
fails to follow credible evidence about
the whereabouts of a known fugitive?

1075
01:30:34,370 --> 01:30:36,877
I think there'd be a variety, actually.

1076
01:30:37,651 --> 01:30:39,499
You have information,
why aren't you coming forward?

1077
01:30:41,751 --> 01:30:44,675
Well, you have information too.
So what are you gonna do?

1078
01:30:45,154 --> 01:30:47,679
I'm a journalist.
I'm gonna do what I always do.

1079
01:30:47,775 --> 01:30:50,258
And this information's gonna be on
every computer screen in the next 20 minutes,

1080
01:30:50,259 --> 01:30:51,890
and I'm gonna find out everything
you're hiding from me,

1081
01:30:51,891 --> 01:30:55,208
and I'm gonna expose it in a very big and very real way.

1082
01:30:56,663 --> 01:30:59,000
You're about to do a lot of damage
to a lot of people.

1083
01:31:00,056 --> 01:31:01,786
You've no idea how much.

1084
01:31:03,155 --> 01:31:07,501
I think they have it coming.
- On that, you could not be more wrong.

1085
01:31:08,461 --> 01:31:12,392
Innocent people are about to get
swept up in this storm you're unleashing.

1086
01:31:13,160 --> 01:31:16,053
Trust me.
- Trust you...?

1087
01:31:16,766 --> 01:31:18,105
Tell me something, Mr Osborne.

1088
01:31:18,106 --> 01:31:20,501
Are you one of those innocent people?
- No, I am not.

1089
01:31:22,769 --> 01:31:24,403
But my daughter is.

1090
01:31:26,070 --> 01:31:27,307
How so?

1091
01:31:34,070 --> 01:31:35,711
I got somethin' I need to do,

1092
01:31:37,279 --> 01:31:39,855
but on my own terms.

1093
01:32:03,266 --> 01:32:04,752
Upper peninsula.

1094
01:32:13,071 --> 01:32:15,930
'Becc, it's Dad.
I'm trying you again.

1095
01:32:16,534 --> 01:32:19,558
Um... sorry about the messages.

1096
01:32:20,250 --> 01:32:21,403
uh...

1097
01:32:21,500 --> 01:32:26,300
Listen, if you... when you get a chance,
I need to talk to you, to tell you...

1098
01:32:27,478 --> 01:32:30,971
this... Shepard guy, um...

1099
01:32:32,275 --> 01:32:34,760
uh, it's important, 'Becc.

1100
01:32:35,588 --> 01:32:38,996
I love you, sweetie.
Call me back, please.

1101
01:32:43,276 --> 01:32:46,283
I don't know why that's so hard to figure out.
- What makes you think I was ever gonna be...

1102
01:32:46,284 --> 01:32:48,880
For one thing, I didn't do it.
I wasn't there, Mimi.

1103
01:32:48,977 --> 01:32:51,004
But you should have been,
then everything would have been different.

1104
01:32:51,485 --> 01:32:56,494
Vince lost his cool, completely.
You wouldn't have, nobody would've gotten hurt.

1105
01:32:56,495 --> 01:33:00,981
Somebody didn't get hurt, somebody got killed.
A father, a husband, with a family.

1106
01:33:00,982 --> 01:33:04,333
You think I didn't think about that when
so many fathers with families were being killed?

1107
01:33:04,334 --> 01:33:05,475
And still are!

1108
01:33:05,487 --> 01:33:07,430
You shouldn't have gone, Mimi.
You should've said no.

1109
01:33:09,974 --> 01:33:11,714
We were done.
- No. You were done.

1110
01:33:12,386 --> 01:33:15,540
I never was, but you couldn't accept that.
- Mimi...

1111
01:33:16,691 --> 01:33:19,327
You fooled yourself into thinking
I was someone else.

1112
01:33:20,579 --> 01:33:21,435
And you're still doing it.

1113
01:33:23,080 --> 01:33:27,187
I am not the one fooling myself, it was over!
-  It wasn't... over.

1114
01:33:27,380 --> 01:33:29,199
It's still not over.

1115
01:33:29,584 --> 01:33:31,587
Every single thing we said
then, is true today.

1116
01:33:31,685 --> 01:33:34,704
And every single day, it's getting worse.
- That's not the point.

1117
01:33:34,737 --> 01:33:36,977
Oh, it's exactly the point, Nick!

1118
01:33:38,321 --> 01:33:41,448
I won't give myself up
to a system I despise.

1119
01:33:42,314 --> 01:33:45,674
I won't give up my freedom and accept
their version of what life is supposed to be.

1120
01:33:45,674 --> 01:33:49,513
Mimi, how free are you? Really?
- Well, I'm not in jail.

1121
01:33:50,494 --> 01:33:53,314
I don't expect you to understand.
They have you.

1122
01:33:53,315 --> 01:33:54,275
Oh, like hell.

1123
01:33:54,322 --> 01:33:58,902
A system that protects the super-rich,
and the super, super, super-rich,

1124
01:33:58,903 --> 01:34:02,902
And fucks over everyone else, and the planet to boot.
- Mimi... Mimi, would you just stop?

1125
01:34:03,574 --> 01:34:08,494
Everyone who's given up and given in,
they're living at the expense of what they once believed.

1126
01:34:08,495 --> 01:34:12,311
It's so sad!
You understood this,

1127
01:34:12,888 --> 01:34:15,712
I'm sorry you've forgotten.
- I wish I had forgotten!

1128
01:34:16,096 --> 01:34:18,323
Because my problem is
I can't stop remembering.

1129
01:34:18,516 --> 01:34:22,495
So if you've built a wall so high, more power
to you, you're stronger than I am.

1130
01:34:22,506 --> 01:34:24,108
I'm will turn myself in...

1131
01:34:24,888 --> 01:34:29,796
the day the politicians and corporations
turn themselves in for all they've done.

1132
01:34:30,085 --> 01:34:32,948
That's the day I'll hand myself in.
Scout's fuckin' honor.

1133
01:34:33,045 --> 01:34:36,021
Stop hiding behind your fucking revolutionary rant.
- Oh, don't turn it on me.

1134
01:34:36,117 --> 01:34:37,514
You know what I see?

1135
01:34:37,998 --> 01:34:41,241
I see the same person.
I see it, kid.

1136
01:34:42,498 --> 01:34:44,498
I see it in your eyes.

1137
01:34:46,295 --> 01:34:50,327
You can hide from everyone else in the world,
and be somebody else, but not with me.

1138
01:34:51,483 --> 01:34:54,503
What are your memories, Mi?
The ones you can't run away from.

1139
01:34:54,696 --> 01:34:55,656
Hey!

1140
01:34:58,274 --> 01:35:00,512
We had a responsibility beyond the cause.

1141
01:35:01,280 --> 01:35:02,610
We had a baby.

1142
01:35:07,704 --> 01:35:10,645
We were so consumed by our principles,

1143
01:35:11,996 --> 01:35:14,633
that we abandoned our most
fundamental duty.

1144
01:35:19,777 --> 01:35:21,817
We were doing our duty, Nick.

1145
01:35:22,877 --> 01:35:26,077
We made a plan, that if anything ever went wrong,
- Never should have carried out that plan.

1146
01:35:26,077 --> 01:35:28,315
we would know exactly
what we had to do.

1147
01:35:28,698 --> 01:35:30,718
We both agreed.
- We were wrong.

1148
01:35:31,490 --> 01:35:34,130
We had no choice.
- We should have known that we were wrong.

1149
01:35:37,191 --> 01:35:38,711
We both accepted it,

1150
01:35:39,991 --> 01:35:41,440
and we both had to live with it.

1151
01:36:22,297 --> 01:36:23,542
It wasn't a dream...

1152
01:36:25,698 --> 01:36:31,702
it was a possibility,
we could have made a reality.

1153
01:36:32,599 --> 01:36:36,379
We could make them stop.

1154
01:36:37,204 --> 01:36:40,180
Yeah, we could change things,

1155
01:36:41,092 --> 01:36:42,540
if we could make a difference.

1156
01:36:44,691 --> 01:36:46,288
I still believe in that possibility.

1157
01:36:59,585 --> 01:37:01,442
Is that all you believe?

1158
01:37:10,410 --> 01:37:12,726
Can you put me through to
Ben Shepard please?

1159
01:37:14,686 --> 01:37:17,374
(Aw, shit!)
Rebecca!

1160
01:37:18,047 --> 01:37:20,531
What did you say to my dad?
He sounds really upset.

1161
01:37:21,407 --> 01:37:24,106
What do you mean?
- He left me a dozen voice messages last night,

1162
01:37:24,107 --> 01:37:25,355
he said it had to do with you.

1163
01:37:26,411 --> 01:37:31,016
What is going on?
- You're gonna have to talk to your father.

1164
01:37:44,309 --> 01:37:45,641
You're up.

1165
01:37:47,809 --> 01:37:52,153
I remember when these trees were so small,
you could see clear across the water.

1166
01:37:57,805 --> 01:37:59,139
I saw her.

1167
01:38:01,918 --> 01:38:03,231
What?

1168
01:38:07,812 --> 01:38:10,535
I've went to do Ann Arbor on my way...

1169
01:38:11,611 --> 01:38:14,334
I didn't want to.
I just...

1170
01:38:14,632 --> 01:38:17,228
couldn't help myself.

1171
01:38:20,212 --> 01:38:24,641
I sat in my car like
some kind of stalker.

1172
01:38:25,986 --> 01:38:27,233
Mim.

1173
01:38:32,113 --> 01:38:34,829
She's really something, Nicky.

1174
01:38:36,817 --> 01:38:38,230
Truly.

1175
01:38:43,614 --> 01:38:45,634
We always intended to
tell you the truth.

1176
01:38:46,017 --> 01:38:47,722
You always intended...?

1177
01:38:49,806 --> 01:38:53,670
At the time we felt...
- We hoped that nobody needed to know.

1178
01:38:56,111 --> 01:38:58,459
I never asked about my birth parents,

1179
01:38:59,516 --> 01:39:01,319
I really never needed to know.

1180
01:39:01,415 --> 01:39:05,435
We know. There's no way
to make this easier.

1181
01:39:06,012 --> 01:39:08,922
We redid your identity,
papered a legal adoption.

1182
01:39:09,116 --> 01:39:10,553
None of that matters to me.

1183
01:39:12,696 --> 01:39:14,553
Did you think I
couldn't handle it?

1184
01:39:15,225 --> 01:39:17,144
Sweetie, we gotta talk through this.

1185
01:39:21,613 --> 01:39:23,517
No one's perfect, 'Becc.

1186
01:39:25,213 --> 01:39:27,025
I love you

1187
01:39:30,898 --> 01:39:32,522
I love you too.

1188
01:39:56,816 --> 01:39:58,576
I can't do what you
want me to do, Nicky.

1189
01:40:00,015 --> 01:40:01,028
I know.

1190
01:40:03,112 --> 01:40:06,464
I guess I was hoping you would
become the person who could.

1191
01:40:11,117 --> 01:40:12,533
So it goes.

1192
01:40:35,118 --> 01:40:38,542
Sir, the local K-9 units are on the way.
- Roger that.

1193
01:40:43,724 --> 01:40:45,034
Hello?

1194
01:40:48,219 --> 01:40:49,648
I'm here alone!

1195
01:40:52,020 --> 01:40:53,232
Hello?

1196
01:40:55,320 --> 01:40:56,572
You?!

1197
01:40:57,628 --> 01:40:59,153
You expecting to see somebody else?

1198
01:41:01,825 --> 01:41:04,428
She here?
- Who're we talking about?

1199
01:41:04,525 --> 01:41:08,168
Who're we talkin' about. Mimi Lurie!
That's who you came to see, right?

1200
01:41:08,457 --> 01:41:11,350
Huh?
- Mimi Lurie. That's who you came to see, correct?

1201
01:41:11,542 --> 01:41:13,175
Why would I do that?
- She could testify that you weren't at the bank.

1202
01:41:13,366 --> 01:41:15,546
Almost sounds like a news story, doesn't it?

1203
01:41:16,618 --> 01:41:20,246
Unfortunately, I need a source.
- Really? Must be a new policy.

1204
01:41:21,022 --> 01:41:22,239
Is she here, Nick?

1205
01:41:23,023 --> 01:41:24,254
She never was.

1206
01:41:28,910 --> 01:41:30,723
You call 'em?
- No.

1207
01:41:35,124 --> 01:41:39,244
Well you got yourself a story, kid. Congratulations.
I hope you're satisfied.

1208
01:41:39,827 --> 01:41:42,434
I don't wanna see a guy go to jail for the
rest of his life for something he didn't do.

1209
01:41:42,628 --> 01:41:46,141
Is that what passes for idealism these days?
- Is Mimi gonna surrender?

1210
01:41:47,028 --> 01:41:49,532
No.
- No. So, where are you going?

1211
01:41:49,724 --> 01:41:52,332
Well, before she can not surrender,
she has to first not get caught.

1212
01:41:52,525 --> 01:41:53,958
I don't understand, there
was an easier way.

1213
01:41:54,633 --> 01:41:55,845
Usually is.

1214
01:41:56,925 --> 01:41:58,854
You'll learn that lesson.

1215
01:41:59,430 --> 01:42:00,953
You know, I met your daughter.

1216
01:42:04,826 --> 01:42:06,434
Your older daughter.

1217
01:42:08,534 --> 01:42:11,535
Then you really do have yourself a story, don't ya'?

1218
01:42:11,922 --> 01:42:14,299
I'm guessing you didn't just stumble into this information...

1219
01:42:14,492 --> 01:42:15,740
by my count, there are exactly

1220
01:42:16,128 --> 01:42:17,907
four people on the planet that...

1221
01:42:18,100 --> 01:42:19,251
knew about this...

1222
01:42:21,627 --> 01:42:26,255
You get let in on something like this, Ben...
you get answers, but not the ones you think.

1223
01:42:26,736 --> 01:42:28,172
Secrets are a dangerous thing, Ben.

1224
01:42:29,229 --> 01:42:31,761
We all think we want to know them,
but if you've kept one to yourself...

1225
01:42:32,336 --> 01:42:35,775
You come to understand that doing so means that
you may learn something about somebody else,

1226
01:42:36,640 --> 01:42:39,170
but you also discover something about yourself.

1227
01:42:40,332 --> 01:42:41,661
I hope you're ready for that.

1228
01:42:43,009 --> 01:42:45,353
At this point,
I have no more secrets.

1229
01:42:47,125 --> 01:42:48,166
You're a smart guy...

1230
01:42:49,029 --> 01:42:50,350
Hold on, I'm not gonna hurt you.

1231
01:42:51,030 --> 01:42:53,942
You know exactly what motivates me,
and has for the last thirty years.

1232
01:42:54,038 --> 01:42:56,641
What you're gonna have to
figure out, is what motivates you.

1233
01:42:57,026 --> 01:43:00,234
I hope you like the answer.
- Hold on. Nick. Nick!

1234
01:43:00,234 --> 01:43:03,903
When the FBI comes, they'll follow me.
They'll never know she was here.

1235
01:43:18,236 --> 01:43:19,449
There he is.

1236
01:44:25,441 --> 01:44:29,714
What's that? That's it.
Come on! Come on.

1237
01:44:33,614 --> 01:44:38,155
Alright... we'll take up, you guys flank around from there.

1238
01:45:20,141 --> 01:45:20,893
There he is!

1239
01:45:26,946 --> 01:45:28,258
Nicholas Sloan!

1240
01:45:29,647 --> 01:45:35,232
You're under arrest for the
murder of Hugh Kroessna.

1241
01:45:44,044 --> 01:45:46,060
Can't say I'm happy to see you.

1242
01:47:19,335 --> 01:47:23,279
Mimi Lurie, last remaining fugitive
from the 1980 Bank of Michigan robbery,

1243
01:47:23,376 --> 01:47:26,635
surrendered herself to authorities today
near Drummond Island, Michigan,

1244
01:47:26,732 --> 01:47:28,555
just across the water from Canada.

1245
01:47:28,651 --> 01:47:32,567
She confessed to her role in the robbery, which
resulted in the death of a guard.

1246
01:47:32,856 --> 01:47:35,073
Charges have been dropped against Nicholas Sloan,

1247
01:47:35,265 --> 01:47:38,067
long thought to be a co-conspirator
in the robbery.

1248
01:47:38,165 --> 01:47:43,441
No comment yet from Sloan, who is expected
to be released from custody as early as tomorrow.

1249
01:47:43,538 --> 01:47:44,594
In other news today...

1250
01:48:44,062 --> 01:48:46,639
I have nothing to say.